{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T17:23:18.149Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of Thought (CoT) prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" is a technique where you ask the model to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generate intermediate reasoning steps"},{"type":"text","text":" before producing the final answer. Instead of jumping directly to an answer, the model \"thinks out loud\" — breaking complex problems into smaller, logical chunks that mirror how humans approach decisions requiring thought."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key insight: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generating a chain of thought—a series of intermediate reasoning steps—significantly improves the ability of large language models to perform complex reasoning."},{"type":"text","text":" This is especially important for tasks that require multi-step logic."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Chain of Thought Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of Thought (CoT) prompting is a technique where the model generates step-by-step intermediate explanations before arriving at an answer."},{"type":"text","text":" This helps improve accuracy and makes the output clearer and more reliable."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The core mechanism:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input"},{"type":"text","text":" → Question or task\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Intermediate steps"},{"type":"text","text":" → Chain of thought (reasoning)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output"},{"type":"text","text":" → Final answer"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike standard prompting where the model jumps from input to output, CoT adds a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"visible reasoning layer"},{"type":"text","text":" in between."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Let Claude Think? (The Big Benefits)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dramatically Improved Accuracy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain of thought prompting "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"improves performance on arithmetic, commonsense, and symbolic reasoning tasks"},{"type":"text","text":". The empirical gains can be striking."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Math Problem"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Without CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"Jenny has 6 oranges. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny. How many oranges does Jaime have?\"\nAnswer: 8 (WRONG - model jumped to answer)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ With CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"Jenny has 6 oranges. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny. How many oranges does Jaime have?\"\n\nLet's think step by step:\n1. Jenny has 6 oranges.\n2. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny.\n3. \"2 fewer than 6\" means: 6 - 2 = 4\n4. Therefore, Jaime has 4 oranges.\n\nAnswer: 4 (CORRECT)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key finding:"},{"type":"text","text":" Prompting a 540B-parameter language model with just "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"eight chain of thought exemplars"},{"type":"text","text":" achieves state-of-the-art accuracy on the GSM8K benchmark of math word problems, surpassing even finetuned GPT-3 with a verifier."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Transparency & Debuggability"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can follow the AI's reasoning, which makes it easier to trust — or debug if something goes wrong."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Output: \"The answer is 42.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You have no way to verify if this is correct or how it was derived."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Calculate total cost = $50 × 2 = $100\nStep 2: Apply 20% discount = $100 × 0.20 = $20\nStep 3: Final price = $100 - $20 = $80\nStep 4: Split among 3 people = $80 ÷ 3 = $26.67 per person\n\nAnswer: $26.67 per person"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can trace each step, verify the math, and identify where errors occur."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Makes the reasoning process visible"},{"type":"text","text":" to users\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Helps in understanding"},{"type":"text","text":" how the final answer is derived\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Increases trust"},{"type":"text","text":" in model outputs"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduced Hallucinations"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear reasoning reduces the chance of AI \"hallucinations,\" or making up facts that sound convincing but are false."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"},{"type":"text","text":" By focusing on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"intermediate steps"},{"type":"text","text":", the model can make fewer mistakes and provide more accurate results. The transparency helps users understand the reasoning behind the output."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"What year did the Mars Perseverance rover land?\"\nAnswer: \"2024 (WRONG - hallucinated)\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With CoT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let's think step by step:\n1. The Mars Perseverance rover is NASA's latest Mars mission.\n2. I recall it landed in early 2021.\n3. Let me verify: February 18, 2021 was the landing date.\n4. Therefore, the answer is 2021.\n\nAnswer: 2021 (CORRECT)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Better Handling of Complex, Multi-Step Tasks"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain of thought reasoning allows models to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"decompose complex problems into intermediate steps that are solved individually."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"This approach is particularly helpful for:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt engineering"},{"type":"text","text":": Design prompts that guide AI to use CoT, improving how it handles tough questions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-shot learning"},{"type":"text","text":": Show the AI a few examples of step-by-step reasoning to \"teach\" it the pattern\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Advanced tasks"},{"type":"text","text":": Decision trees, troubleshooting, planning, layered logic (diagnosing bugs, suggesting next-best-actions)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Avoids \"Irrational Leaps\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The model is less likely to make irrational leaps or skip important steps."},{"type":"text","text":" Especially helpful in math, logic, and planning tasks."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without CoT (skips steps):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"If a train travels 60 miles in 1.5 hours, what's its speed?\"\nAnswer: \"40 mph\" (Correct, but model may have guessed)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With CoT (shows work):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Speed = Distance ÷ Time\nStep 2: Distance = 60 miles\nStep 3: Time = 1.5 hours\nStep 4: Speed = 60 ÷ 1.5 = 40 mph\n\nAnswer: 40 mph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model can't skip the formula, so it's forced to reason through the problem."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Chain of Thought Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Two Main Approaches"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Zero-Shot CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" (Simple)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Just add "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Let's think step by step\""},{"type":"text","text":" to your prompt. This is the zero-shot CoT approach (Kojima et al. 2022)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"Jenny has 6 oranges. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny. How many does Jaime have?\"\nAssistant: \"Let's think step by step... [reasoning steps]... Answer: 4\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"},{"type":"text","text":" Even without examples, the phrase \"let's think step by step\" prompts the model to generate reasoning steps."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Few-Shot CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" (More Powerful)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"few-shot demonstrations"},{"type":"text","text":" showing the reasoning pattern. This is when you include examples in your prompt of how reasoning steps should look."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"Jenny has 6 oranges. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny. How many does Jaime have?\"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Jenny has 6 oranges.\n2. Jaime has 2 fewer than Jenny.\n3. 6 - 2 = 4.\n\nAnswer: 4\n\n---\n\nQuestion: \"Tom has 10 apples. He gives 3 to Sarah and buys 5 more. How many does he have now?\"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Tom starts with 10 apples.\n2. He gives 3 to Sarah: 10 - 3 = 7.\n3. He buys 5 more: 7 + 5 = 12.\n\nAnswer: 12\n\n---\n\nQuestion: \"Maria has 8 books. She loses 2 and buys 4 more. How many does she have?\"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Maria starts with 8 books.\n2. She loses 2: 8 - 2 = 6.\n3. She buys 4 more: 6 + 4 = 10.\n\nAnswer: ?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model learns the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" from the examples and applies it to the new question."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Works (The Science)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of thought reasoning is an emergent property of model scale"},{"type":"text","text":" — the benefits only materialize with sufficient model parameters (around 100B). Language models of sufficient scale (~100B parameters) can solve complex reasoning problems that are not solvable with standard prompting methods."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The mechanism:"},{"type":"text","text":" The model-generated chain of thought "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"mimics an intuitive thought process"},{"type":"text","text":" when working through a multi-step reasoning problem. It decomposes complex problems into smaller steps that are solved individually."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use Chain of Thought"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use CoT When:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Math & Arithmetic"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Solving multi-step equations, percentage problems"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Logic Puzzles"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reasoning problems requiring deduction"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Planning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-step decision trees, troubleshooting"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multi-hop QA"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Questions requiring chained reasoning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex Analysis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Layered logic, deep reasoning tasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Code Debugging"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Walking through code execution step-by-step"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for tasks that require multi-step reasoning."},{"type":"text","text":" CoT drastically improves performance in math, logic puzzles, reasoning tasks, and multi-hop question answering."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Skip CoT When:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task Type"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple Facts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"What's the capital of France?\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic Classification"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Is this email spam or not?\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Quick Summaries"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this 100-word article\" (short)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Translation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Translate 'hello' to Spanish\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Straightforward QA"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Who wrote Hamlet?\""}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"TL;DR:"},{"type":"text","text":" Chain-of-thought makes AI \"show its work\" before giving an answer. It's not always necessary, but when it is, it's transformative."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use CoT when you need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":", not just facts."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Implement Chain of Thought"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 1: Simple \"Think Step by Step\""}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"A bakery sells 3 types of cookies: chocolate, vanilla, and almond. They sell 15 chocolate, 20 vanilla, and 10 almond cookies per day. How many cookies do they sell in 5 days?\"\n\nAssistant: \"Let's think step by step:\n1. First, calculate total cookies per day: 15 + 20 + 10 = 45\n2. Then, multiply by 5 days: 45 × 5 = 225\n\nAnswer: 225 cookies\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 2: Few-Shot with Examples"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1:\nQuestion: \"John has 5 apples. He buys 3 more and eats 2. How many does he have?\"\nReasoning:\n- Start with 5 apples\n- Buy 3 more: 5 + 3 = 8\n- Eat 2: 8 - 2 = 6\nAnswer: 6\n\nExample 2:\nQuestion: \"Sarah has $20. She buys a $5 book and a $3 pen. How much money does she have left?\"\nReasoning:\n- Start with $20\n- Buy book: $20 - $5 = $15\n- Buy pen: $15 - $3 = $12\nAnswer: $12\n\nQuestion: \"Maria has $30. She spends $12 on lunch and $8 on gas. How much is left?\"\nReasoning:"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 3: Using XML Tags (Claude-Specific)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude supports structured reasoning with tags like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<thinking>"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<answer>"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<thinking>\nStep 1: Identify the problem\nStep 2: Break down into sub-steps\nStep 3: Solve each step\nStep 4: Verify the answer\n</thinking>\n\n<answer>\nFinal answer here\n</answer>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced Chain of Thought Variants"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-Consistency CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multiple reasoning chains"},{"type":"text","text":" and choose the most consistent answer. Instead of trusting one reasoning path, ask the model to generate multiple chains and pick the most consistent."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Contrastive CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Show "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"both correct and wrong explanations"},{"type":"text","text":". This shows the model what not to do rather than having \"don't do X, don't do Y\" instructions in your prompt."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Faithful CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate reasoning that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"faithfully follows the facts"},{"type":"text","text":" rather than making up explanations. This ensures the reasoning is accurate."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tabular CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tables"},{"type":"text","text":" to organize reasoning steps. This is helpful for structured data reasoning."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Analogical CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"analogies"},{"type":"text","text":" to generate in-context examples. This helps the model reason by comparing similar problems."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step-Back CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start with a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"higher-level question"},{"type":"text","text":" before diving into details. This provides context for the reasoning."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Thread-of-Thought"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Maintain "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multiple reasoning threads"},{"type":"text","text":" simultaneously. This helps with complex, multi-faceted problems."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes with Chain of Thought"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 1: Not Using It When Needed"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Help me debug this complex multi-function code.\"\n→ Model gives answer directly without showing reasoning"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Help me debug this complex multi-function code. Let's think step by step through each function's execution.\"\n→ Model shows reasoning first"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 2: Using It When Not Needed"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Let's think step by step. What's the capital of France?\"\n→ Overkill for simple fact questions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"What's the capital of France?\"\n→ Direct answer is fine"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 3: Inconsistent Example Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1:\nQuestion: ...\nReasoning: Line 1, Line 2, Line 3\nAnswer: X\n\nExample 2:\nQuestion: ...\nReasoning:\n- Line 1\n- Line 2\nAnswer: Y"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1:\nQuestion: ...\nReasoning:\n- Line 1\n- Line 2\n- Line 3\nAnswer: X\n\nExample 2:\nQuestion: ...\nReasoning:\n- Line 1\n- Line 2\n- Line 3\nAnswer: Y"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep format consistent across all examples."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of Thought (CoT) prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" enables complex reasoning through "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"intermediate reasoning steps"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dramatically improved accuracy"},{"type":"text","text":" — State-of-the-art on math benchmarks, surpassing finetuned models\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Transparency & debuggability"},{"type":"text","text":" — You can follow and verify the reasoning\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduced hallucinations"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear reasoning reduces false facts\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Better multi-step handling"},{"type":"text","text":" — Decomposes complex problems\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Avoids irrational leaps"},{"type":"text","text":" — Forces step-by-step processing"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot CoT"},{"type":"text","text":": Add \"Let's think step by step\" to prompt\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot CoT"},{"type":"text","text":": Provide examples showing reasoning pattern\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mechanism"},{"type":"text","text":": Mimics intuitive thought process, decomposes problems"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- ✅ Math, logic puzzles, planning, multi-hop QA, complex analysis, code debugging\n- ❌ Simple facts, basic classification, quick summaries, translation, straightforward QA"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Advanced variants:"},{"type":"text","text":" Self-Consistency, Contrastive, Faithful, Tabular, Analogical, Step-Back, Thread-of-Thought"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of Thought doesn't make AI \"conscious\" — but it makes them look smarter by mimicking how humans reason step by step."},{"type":"text","text":" It enhances the model's ability to tackle tasks requiring multi-step reasoning, including mathematical operations, logical deduction, and commonsense reasoning."}]}]}}
